    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the<strong> cardamom seeds </strong>to a <strong>food processor </strong>with the <strong>pistachios</strong>, <strong>cracked black pepper</strong>, <strong>chopped garlic </strong>and <strong>chopped ginger</strong></p><p>Add most<strong> </strong>of the <strong>chopped coriander </strong>(save some for garnish!) and <strong>half </strong>the <strong>chopped chilli </strong>(can't handle the heat? Go easy!) with 100ml <span class=\"text-danger\">[150ml]</span><strong> cold water </strong>and a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and blitz until smooth – this is your <strong>curry paste</strong></p><p>Once the onion has softened, add the <strong>curry paste </strong>and <strong>butternut squash cubes </strong>to the pan<strong> </strong>and cook for 2-3 min or until fragrant</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
